### Software PRD Sections (what the script produces)

The script generates the PRD in this order:

**Header** — Project name, company, business unit, PM, date, version

**1. Introduction** — Background, business context, the opportunity, predecessor systems, what makes this the right time

**2. Goals** — Primary goals with success metrics; secondary goals; explicit out-of-scope exclusions

**3. Business Outputs** — Expected business outcomes (revenue, cost, efficiency, compliance); how success is measured post-launch; key stakeholder benefits

**4. Stakeholders** — Table: Group | Role | Needs | Constraints. Standard groups: End Users, Product Owner/Sponsor, Engineering/Architecture, Security & Compliance, Operations/SRE, Customer Service, Marketing & Sales, Legal/Regulatory.

**5. User Stories** — 2–5 personas. Each: story sentence ("As a…") + 1–2 paragraph narrative. Stories should motivate the requirements that follow.

**6. Technical Strategy** — Architecture pattern, technology choices with rationale, integration patterns, data strategy, migration approach (if any), engineering principles. This explains *how* the team will build it.

**7. Requirements (Aspects)** — Structured requirements with **P1–P10 priority scoring** (P10 = must-have at launch, P1 = nice-to-have). Standard aspects for software:
- 7.1 Functional Requirements
- 7.2 User Experience & Interface
- 7.3 Performance & Scalability
- 7.4 Integrations & APIs
- 7.5 Data & Storage
- 7.6 Security & Compliance
- 7.7 Infrastructure & Deployment

Format: `7.1.1  The system shall [requirement].  (P9)`

Good requirements are testable. "Respond within 200ms at P95 under 1000 concurrent users" is testable. "Be fast" is not. Flag vague requirements in the Action List.

**8. Dependencies** — Table: Dependency | Type | Owner | Status | Risk if Delayed

**9. Monitoring & Security** — Two subsections: Observability (logging, metrics, tracing, alerting, incident response) and Security Controls (auth model, encryption, secrets management, vulnerability scanning, pen testing, pipeline security gates)

**10. Milestones** — Table: Milestone | Target Date | Owner | Notes

