## Step 5: Generate the TPM Action List

After the PRD, produce a separate **TPM Action List** as a second `.docx` file using the same `build_prd.js` script with `--action-list` flag, or as a `.md` file if docx generation has any issues.

This is for the TPM's internal use — preparing for PRD review meetings, stakeholder discussions, and sprint planning.

### TPM Action List Structure

```
TPM Action List — [Project Name]
Generated: [date]

OPEN QUESTIONS ([N] items)
Things that need an answer before or during implementation.
Table: # | Question | Relevant PRD Section | Who Can Answer | Priority

RISKS ([N] items)  
Identified threats to delivery, quality, or adoption.
Table: # | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Suggested Mitigation | Relevant PRD Section

PENDING DECISIONS ([N] items)
Choices that need stakeholder alignment before the PRD can be locked.
Table: # | Decision | Options | Recommended By | Deadline | Relevant PRD Section
```

At the top of the Action List, include a short header note:
> *"This Action List was generated alongside your PRD. Use it to prepare for PRD review sessions with stakeholders — work through these items to fortify the plan. Once resolved, document outcomes in the relevant PRD section and remove from this list."*

