## Step 6: Create the Live Change Desk Artifact

Create a Cowork artifact using `mcp__cowork__create_artifact`. This is the TPM's tool for understanding the blast radius of incoming requirement changes.

### What the artifact does

1. Shows the 10 PRD sections with their completion status (populated / partial / TBD)
2. Provides a text input where the TPM describes an incoming change
3. When the TPM submits, calls `window.cowork.askClaude()` to analyse which sections are likely impacted
4. Displays a structured impact summary: affected section → what changes → why → magnitude (High / Medium / Low)

### Embedding PRD context in the artifact

When creating the artifact, embed a `prdSections` data object containing a one-sentence summary of each section's current content. This gives Claude enough context to reason about impact without needing to re-read the full document.

Pass this data to `askClaude()` alongside the change description:
```javascript
const result = await window.cowork.askClaude(
  `A requirement change has been raised for this software project. 
   Analyse which sections of the PRD are likely impacted and why.
   For each affected section, state: what changes, why it's affected, 
   and the magnitude of impact (High/Medium/Low).
   
   Incoming change: ${changeDescription}
   
   PRD sections:
   ${JSON.stringify(prdSections, null, 2)}`,
  []
);
```

### Important note in the artifact

Include this callout visibly in the artifact UI:
> *"This Change Desk shows the likely impact of a change — it doesn't make edits. Once you've discussed the impact with your stakeholders, come back to Claude to collaborate on the specific PRD amendments."*

